[{"id":"VR610777","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a graph of line segment in the first quadrant of the x y plane with the origin labeled O. The line segment is labeled with its length B. Line segment B begins at the origin, which represents a school. The line segment slants upward and to the right until it ends at a point that is far above the x axis, and far to the right of the y axis. This end point represents a student’s house.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR610777.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In relation to a school, a student’s house is located at a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>B</mi></math></span></span> away and at an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> from the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-axis in the coordinate system shown in the figure. Starting from the school, the student takes a bus and travels a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>A</mi></math></span></span> in the positive <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi></math></span></span>-direction, and then gets off the bus. What is the position vector <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"vector r\"><math alttext=\"vector r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>r</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span></span> of the student’s house relative to where